Title: Star Trek Beyond Official Trailer #2 (2016) - Chris Pine, Zachary Quinto Movie HD
Comment:
There were many things about this Star Trek that were an improvment from recent attempts.  I especially liked the view of the Enterprise at warp showing the nacels creating waves in reality.  

Hovever, as a follower of the Trek since the beginning, there is something about this movie that kicked me right out of the story.  Somewhere around 50 minutes into Beyond, the saucer section lifts by a bunch of things that look like old rocket booster flames.  THE ENTERPRISE MOVES SUB-LIGHT VIA REACTIONLESS THRUSTERS, it always has.  Reactionless thrusters like the tie fighters in Star Wars, not reaction thrusters like on a present day rocket.  The effect is like watching that old classic The Sea Witch, and see as the ship goes by, that it's powered by a couple of outboard motors.  Dissapointing.

This movie is going to be great, and here's why: it's the first film in this series not to 1) have to set up the characters, and 2) isn't using old material. It's a fresh new adventure, almost like a long, dramatic and emotional episode of Star Trek. 

On the other hand I feel the same way about Insurrection... one of the least favorite Star Trek films among fans. Frankly I loved that it wasn't about the fate of the galaxy hanging in the balance for a change, and just the crew of the Enterprise at stake.
